news.title: Trump to start final Fed chair interviews beginning with Kevin Warsh
news.summary: President Donald Trump will begin the final interviews of candidates for the Federal Reserve chair this week. The formal selection process began this summer and is expected to last until the end of the year.

news.title: The Fed decision is expected to feature a rate cut and a lot more. Here's what to expect
news.summary: The central bank is poised to deliver its third straight interest rate cut Wednesday. The bank is also firing a warning shot about what's ahead. The rate cut is expected to be the third in a row.

news.title: Trump trade rep changes China soybean purchase timeline, cites 'discrepancy'
news.summary: China for months earlier this year had boycotted purchasing soybeans from U.S. farms because of a trade war began by President Donald Trump.

news.title: Refinance demand for FHA loans jumps 24%, as homeowners seek the most savings they can
news.summary: Current homeowners are turning to government FHA loans, which offer lower interest rates. The move is seen as a way to find savings, as conventional rates turn higher.

news.title: Walmart and Alquist strike landmark deal, jump-starting 3D-printed commercial real estate
news.summary: The new technology has started to grow in the homebuilding market, but has been far slower in commercial construction. The new technology will be used in the construction of new homes and businesses.

news.title: What happens when your insurer owns your doctor — and why that’s a problem
news.summary: Health insurers increasingly employ the doctors who provide the medical care they pay for. This creates a conflict of interest for the insurers, who pay the doctors for the care.

news.title: GE Vernova is riding the electrification wave, and the stock soars to a record
news.summary: GE Vernova’s stock soars into record territory after the electrification company boosts its long-term outlook for financial returns and plans to return more cash to shareholders.

news.title: Here’s a much better way to make money investing in dividend stocks
news.summary: The ‘Dogs of the Dow’ strategy has been muzzled — check out the ‘Timely Ten.’

news.title: Industrials stocks have been red-hot this year — mostly. One analyst explains which stocks to buy and which to avoid.
news.summary: Nigel Coe of Wolfe Research says industrials have been a hot sector this year, but it’s a stock pickers market.

news.title: There’s a growing healthcare crisis in the U.S. — and it’s sitting in your medicine cabinet
news.summary: To guarantee Americans the medication they need, the U.S. must stop relying on China and India, says Dr. Sanjay Gupta.
